Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement
Rule 2     program -> LABEL COLUMN NEWLINE
Rule 3     program -> NEWLINE
Rule 4     program -> <empty>
Rule 5     statement -> DIRECTIVE IMMEDIATE NEWLINE
Rule 6     statement -> DIRECTIVE NEWLINE
Rule 7     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA register NEWLINE
Rule 8     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA IMMEDIATE NEWLINE
Rule 9     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA IMMEDIATE LPAREN register RPAREN NEWLINE
Rule 10    statement -> OPCODE register COMMA IMMEDIATE NEWLINE
Rule 11    statement -> OPCODE register COMMA LABEL NEWLINE
Rule 12    statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA LABEL NEWLINE
Rule 13    register -> REGISTER
Rule 14    statement -> NEWLINE

Terminals, with rules where they appear

COLUMN               : 2
COMMA                : 7 7 8 8 9 10 11 12 12
DIRECTIVE            : 5 6
IMMEDIATE            : 5 8 9 10
LABEL                : 2 11 12
LPAREN               : 9
NEWLINE              : 2 3 5 6 7 8 9 10 11 12 14
OPCODE               : 7 8 9 10 11 12
REGISTER             : 13
RPAREN               : 9
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

program              : 0
register             : 7 7 7 8 8 9 9 10 11 12 12
statement            : 1

Parsing method: LALR

